<item>
            <title>[SOLR-10316] Unloading a core can remove a ZK SolrCore registration entry for the wrong SolrCore.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-10316</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We only use core node name and collection to match in ZK#unregister(core).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means if a registration was taken over (either via manual user interaction or auto add replicas), unloading a core can remove a ZK entry it should not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
